<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>15588</id>
    <title>IE Scrolling Issue (up &amp; down arrow keys) scrolls entire page</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">If you have a Flash app that has a game which requires using the up &amp; down arrow keys_ IE will scroll the entire window when you push the keys.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">I did have a fix that worked by making the container have the overflow set to auto_ but something changed recently and it no longer works.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I have tried to use JS to stop the page scrolling_ but that solution was a dead end that does not work.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I have tried to set focus to a text field in AS3_ another dead end for our application.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">It works if you have the wmode set to window_ but then you have the problem with Facebook s drop down displaying behind the Flash object.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">In other words... another dead end.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">This would also reduce performance.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">For the app settings:
Canvas Type: Iframe
Iframe Size: Auto resize</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">I have searched high and low inside the Facebook dev forums_ and the bugs here.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">I have not been able to find a solution.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
